{"type":"message","id":"e9371ed4","parentId":"7be59486","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:03:19.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a new session, and I need to greet the user. Let me check the workspace files to understand my persona and identity.\n\nLooking at the workspace context:\n- SOUL.md defines who I am - I should be genuinely helpful, have opinions, be resourceful, earn trust through competence\n- IDENTITY.md is where I define my name, creature type, vibe, and emoji\n- USER.md is about the user\n\nHowever, looking at the actual files in the context:\n- IDENTITY.md has placeholder text - it says \"Fill this in during your first conversation\"\n- USER.md also has placeholder text\n- BOOTSTRAP.md exists and suggests I should figure out who I am with the user\n\nSince BOOTSTRAP.md still exists and IDENTITY.md is empty/placeholder, this suggests this is still the first conversation. But wait - MEMORY.md has content about inventory and cleaning Google Sheets, so there has been some activity.\n\nLet me re-read... BOOTSTRAP.md says \"There is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace\" but MEMORY.md exists with content. This is a bit inconsistent.\n\nActually, looking more carefully:\n- The system says \"A new session was started via /new or /reset\" - this is a session reset, not necessarily a completely new workspace\n- MEMORY.md has content about Google Sheets\n- But IDENTITY.md and USER.md appear to be blank placeholders\n\nGiven this context, I think I should:\n1. Acknowledge the reset\n2. Be myself based on SOUL.md's guidance (genuinely helpful, concise, not performative)\n3. Ask what they want to do\n4. Keep it to 1-3 sentences\n\nI'll be casual and straightforward. No need to interrogate about identity since MEMORY.md suggests there's been prior work done.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey! Fresh session. What do you need help with?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","m