{"type":"message","id":"5a248029","parentId":"34b3c3f0","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:05:52.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! Now I see it. The command object has the key `'Add apartment'` (with a space), and it maps to the `addApartment` function. So the help text was correct, but the command key has a space.\n\nHowever, when I run it from the command line, the shell is splitting \"Add apartment\" into two separate arguments because of the space. Let me check how the argument parsing works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_839a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/google-sheets-api/scripts/src/utils/parseArgs.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":384,"output":211,"cacheRead":19264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19859,"cost":{"input":0.00014592,"output":0.0003587,"cacheRead":0.00366016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00416478}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772100348141}}
{"type":"message","id":"8acb5a0b","parentId":"5a248029","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:05:52.229Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_839a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"'use strict';\r\n\r\nfunction parseArgs(argv) {\r\n  const args = [];\r\n  const flags = {};\r\n\r\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i++) {\r\n    const token = argv[i];\r\n    if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\r\n      args.push(token);\r\n      continue;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    const stripped = token.slice(2);\r\n    const eqIndex = stripped.indexOf('=');\r\n    if (eqIndex >= 0) {\r\n      const key = stripped.slice(0, eqIndex);\r\n      const value = stripped.slice(eqIndex + 1);\r\n      flags[key] = value === '' ? true : value;\r\n      continue;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    const next = argv[i + 1];\r\n    if (next && !next.startsWith('--')) {\r\n      flags[stripped] = next;\r\n      i += 1;\r\n    } else {\r\n      flags[stripped] = true;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return { args, flags };\r\n}\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = { parseArgs };\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772100352217}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a4cb553","parentId":"8acb5a0b","timestamp":"2026-02-26T10:05:57.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The parseArgs function doesn't handle multi-word commands with spaces - it just splits by spaces. So when I pass \"Add apartment 67 Wall 7O\", it becomes:\n- args[0] = \"Add\"\n- args[1] = \"apartment\" \n- args[2] = \"67\"\n- args[3] = \"Wall\"\n- args[4] = \"7O\"\n\nAnd then it looks for commands[\"Add\"], which doesn't exist.\n\nThe issue is that the HELP_TEXT shows \"Add apartment\" as the command name, but the argument parser doesn't support commands with spaces. This seems like a bug in the CLI design.\n\nLooking at the config again, I noticed that in index.js line 27, it checks for `command === 'add-apartment'` (with hyphen). So maybe the actual command name should be \"add-apartment\" instead of \"Add apartment\"? Let me check if there's an \"add-apartment\" entry in the commands object that I might have missed.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the commands/index.js, I don't see 'add-apartment' as a key, only 'Add apartment'. So the HELP_TEXT is wrong or the command registration is wrong.\n\nLet me try using just the hyphenated version:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_13c9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/google-sheets-api ; node scripts/sheets-cli.js add-apartment \"67 Wall 7O\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":3392,"output":576,"cacheRead":16576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20544,"cost":{"input":0.00128896,"output":0.0009792,"cacheRead":0.0031494400000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0054176}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772100352230}}
